@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{faces-extras.el} extends Emacs' built-in @samp{faces} library with a system for programmatically managing face attributes. Emacs faces control the visual appearance of text---fonts, colors, heights, and styles---but configuring them in bulk requires repetitive calls to @code{set-face-attribute}. This package provides a higher-level interface that can apply face settings individually or in batches, store them for later reapplication (for example, after a theme change), and evaluate dynamic values at apply-time.

The package also defines user options for common font and height settings used across fixed-pitch, variable-pitch, and Org mode elements, making it easy to adjust typographic parameters from a single location.

The main capabilities are:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Batch face attribute management.} Functions to set, store, and reapply collections of face attributes (@ref{Setting face attributes}).
@item
@strong{Font and height configuration.} User options for fixed-pitch and variable-pitch fonts, plus Org-specific height adjustments (@ref{Font definitions} and @ref{Height definitions}).
@item
@strong{Enhanced face inspection.} A describe-face variant that disables @code{hl-line-mode} to avoid interference (@ref{Describing faces}).
@item
@strong{Custom face definitions.} A face for the display-time string in the mode line or tab bar (@ref{Display time face}).
@end itemize

