@node Font definitions
@section Font definitions

@vindex faces-extras-variable-pitch-font
The user option @code{faces-extras-variable-pitch-font} specifies the font family for variable-pitch text. You might change this if you prefer a different serif or sans-serif font for prose-heavy buffers such as Org mode or EWW@.

The default value is @samp{"Source Serif Pro"}. The type is a string.

@vindex faces-extras-fixed-pitch-font
The user option @code{faces-extras-fixed-pitch-font} specifies the font family for fixed-pitch text. This is the monospace font used in code buffers, Org source blocks, and similar contexts.

The default value is @samp{"SauceCodePro Nerd Font"}. The type is a string.

@node Height definitions
@section Height definitions

These options define sizes and relative heights for various text elements. Heights are expressed as floating-point multipliers relative to the base font size (e.g., @code{0.8} means 80% of the default height).

@vindex faces-extras-fixed-pitch-size
The user option @code{faces-extras-fixed-pitch-size} specifies the absolute size (in tenths of a point) for fixed-pitch faces. A value of @code{120} corresponds to a 12-point font. The type is an integer. The default value is @code{120}.

@vindex faces-extras-fixed-pitch-height
The user option @code{faces-extras-fixed-pitch-height} specifies the relative height for fixed-pitch faces. This is typically used when fixed-pitch text appears alongside variable-pitch text and needs to be smaller to maintain visual harmony. The type is a number. The default value is @code{0.8}.

@vindex faces-extras-variable-pitch-height
The user option @code{faces-extras-variable-pitch-height} specifies the relative height for variable-pitch faces. A value greater than @code{1.0} makes variable-pitch text larger than the default, which can improve readability for prose. The type is a number. The default value is @code{1.4}.

@vindex faces-extras-org-level-height
The user option @code{faces-extras-org-level-height} controls the relative height for @code{org-level-*} heading faces. The type is a number. The default value is @code{0.9}.

@vindex faces-extras-org-block-height
The user option @code{faces-extras-org-block-height} controls the relative height for the @code{org-block} face, which applies to source blocks and other block elements in Org. The type is a number. The default value is @code{0.8}.

@vindex faces-extras-org-code-height
The user option @code{faces-extras-org-code-height} controls the relative height for the @code{org-code} face. The type is a number. The default value is @code{1.0}.

@vindex faces-extras-org-date-height
The user option @code{faces-extras-org-date-height} controls the relative height for the @code{org-date} face. The type is a number. The default value is @code{0.9}.

@vindex faces-extras-org-tag-height
The user option @code{faces-extras-org-tag-height} controls the relative height for the @code{org-tag} face. The type is a number. The default value is @code{0.9}.

@vindex faces-extras-org-property-value-height
The user option @code{faces-extras-org-property-value-height} controls the relative height for the @code{org-property-value} face. The type is a number. The default value is @code{0.8}.

